 Port Elizabeth - Police in Bethelsdorp, Port Elizabeth, are urgently trying to trace the family of an unidentified man, who passed away at a local hospital on 9 September 2019. According to police information, the 40-year-old black male was taken to Livingstone Hospital on 3 September 2019 with head injuries. "Ambulance services picked him up at about 01:30, near the Booysens Park Community Hall," described police spokesperson, Col Priscilla Naidu. "He passed away on 9 September 2019. "A post mortem report is being awaited." Col Naidu said that police have opened an inquest docket pending the results of the post mortem. "Anyone who can assist police in identifying the man or may know of the circumstances that led to his death is asked to contact D/W/O Wynand Hills at SAPS Bethelsdorp on 041 4043068 or 082 633 1293." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 